Cool Off with This Summer Whiskey Smash

   26Jul


   This summer, take on the warm weather with a cool drink in your hand.
   Try this recipe for a delicious summer whiskey smash, using fresh mint,
   peach, handcrafted whiskey and crushed ice. Watch the video below to
   learn how to plan for your own, then read the instructions to get all
   the ingredients.

   IFRAME: https://www.youtube.com/embed/khNIrFSafX0

   Ingredients:
     * Whiskey
     * Fresh Peaches
     * Mint
     * Lemon Wedges
     * Crushed Ice
     * Store-bought simple syrup

   Directions:
    1. In a glass, add 6-8 mint leaves, 1 lemon wedge and diced peaches.
    2. Add 1.5-oz. of store-bought simple syrup.
    3. Muddle.
    4. Add 2-oz. of your favorite whiskey.
    5. Stir and then add ice.
    6. Garnish with mint sprig and straw and enjoy!

   Inspired to plan your event? Send this ad-free and fully customizable
   Premium Invitation below, and learn more about Evite Pro, the better
   way to manage professional and year-round events.

